  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nContracts have a `sendTransaction` method, which is useful for sending transactions that don't fit any of the contract's methods (or for getting around the current encoder's deficiencies :P ).  However, this only allows one to send custom transactions, not make custom calls or estimate their gas.  Contracts should have `call` and `estimateGas` methods that parallel `sendTransaction`, for when you want to do one of these with a hand-encoded data field.",
